# /etc/logrotate.d/wb-irrigation
# Managed by wb-irrigation repo at configs/logrotate.d/wb-irrigation
# This intentionally owns no paths. Application logs use journald or an
# in-process rotating handler; the retired Telegram file log is purged by the
# native install/update migration. Keeping this managed marker replaces the
# historical stanza on existing controllers and prevents double rotation.
# Deploy scripts refuse activation unless the target Telegram runtime has
# already removed its FileHandler, enforcing that integration order.
